
Overview of verb cruise

The verb cruise has 4 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (3) cruise -- (drive around aimlessly but ostentatiously and at leisure; "She cruised the neighborhood in her new convertible")
2. (2) cruise -- (travel at a moderate speed; "Please keep your seat belt fastened while the plane is reaching cruising altitude")
3. cruise -- (look for a sexual partner in a public place; "The men were cruising the park")
4. cruise -- (sail or travel about for pleasure, relaxation, or sightseeing; "We were cruising in the Caribbean")
